18
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:29,980
= Held in the Lonely Castle =
♪ May the world be peaceful ♪

19
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:33,140
= Episode 55 =

20
00:01:47,260 --> 00:01:48,900
Zhigui,

21
00:01:49,140 --> 00:01:50,900
you have more grey hair than before.

22
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:53,420
= Han Qi, courtesy name Zhigui =

23
00:01:53,420 --> 00:01:54,420
Your Majesty, you

24
00:01:55,140 --> 00:01:56,700
have become emaciated.

25
00:01:58,180 --> 00:01:59,780
Have a seat. Serve tea.

26
00:02:07,620 --> 00:02:08,580
Over the years,

27
00:02:08,740 --> 00:02:10,500
you did disaster relief,
trained troops in Dingzhou

28
00:02:11,180 --> 00:02:12,980
and helped cancel the ban on logging

29
00:02:13,860 --> 00:02:16,780
so that the locals could reclaim wasteland
for farming

30
00:02:17,260 --> 00:02:18,820
and the shortage of arable land was solved.

31
00:02:20,060 --> 00:02:22,340
When you were leaving for Bingzhou,

32
00:02:22,780 --> 00:02:24,220
people of Dingzhou begged you to stay.

33
00:02:24,380 --> 00:02:26,500
You had to make a detour.

34
00:02:27,340 --> 00:02:28,740
All that owes to Your Majesty’s

35
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:30,020
and the locals’ efforts.

36
00:02:30,540 --> 00:02:32,020
I dare not take the credit.

37
00:02:34,860 --> 00:02:35,940
After being a local governor for ten years,

38
00:02:35,940 --> 00:02:37,900
even you have learned to flatter me.

39
00:02:39,180 --> 00:02:40,220
I’ve learned a lot

40
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:41,820
over the past ten years.

41
00:02:42,340 --> 00:02:44,860
I opened up land for farming in Dingzhou.

42
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:46,780
Fu Bi encouraged

43
00:02:47,260 --> 00:02:48,180
the locals in Qingzhou

44
00:02:48,260 --> 00:02:49,900
to harvest products from forests and lakes

45
00:02:50,220 --> 00:02:51,060
and developed trade routes.

46
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:53,420
In Hangzhou, Fan Zhongyan

47
00:02:53,940 --> 00:02:56,060
promoted paying tax with labor

48
00:02:56,340 --> 00:02:57,340
when the region was struck by disasters.

49
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:02,500
Only after becoming local governors

50
00:03:03,180 --> 00:03:05,580
were we able to witness

51
00:03:05,660 --> 00:03:07,700
how policies written on paper

52
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:09,220
were executed in real life

53
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:11,100
and affected farming

54
00:03:11,780 --> 00:03:13,020
and business.

55
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:23,740
Thank you, Your Majesty, for the chance

56
00:03:24,980 --> 00:03:26,580
and your guidance.

57
00:03:31,020 --> 00:03:34,140
Policies were voiced and then followed through.

58
00:03:36,140 --> 00:03:37,520
It’s my pleasure

59
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:42,010
to have met all of you.

60
00:04:18,180 --> 00:04:19,340
Nice harmony

61
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:22,500
amid one wrong note.

62
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,300
Huirou?

63
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:35,980
The tune led me here.

64
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:38,220
I was outside for a while listening to it.

65
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:41,740
The sound of the harp was touching

66
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:42,700
and familiar

67
00:04:43,460 --> 00:04:45,700
